From 92c331eb698792b2df95fbe91e9f493b44c8b57c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Steve Leung <Steve.Leung@amd.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 10:31:23 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] hipsolver: make internal OpenBLAS symbols private (#7176)

## Motivation

542bf80271f9471f878b66af47daee2cd70e9e81 added an internal OpenBLAS
implementation, but accidentally exported all of the BLAS symbols as
public symbols in hipSOLVER.

## Technical Details

Set symbol visibility to hidden for the internal implementation.

## Test Plan

Run regular tests and manually inspect the exported hipSOLVER symbols.

## Test Result

Tests pass, and only hipSOLVER symbols are exported.

## Submission Checklist

- [x] Look over the contributing guidelines at
https://github.com/ROCm/ROCm/blob/develop/CONTRIBUTING.md#pull-requests.
---
 projects/hipsolver/CMakeLists.txt | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/projects/hipsolver/CMakeLists.txt b/projects/hipsolver/CMakeLists.txt
index 6ddbd9c6302..3dce2206a11 100644
--- a/projects/hipsolver/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/projects/hipsolver/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -184,6 +184,7 @@ if(NOT "${HIP_PLATFORM}" STREQUAL "nvidia")
             -DBUILD_BENCHMARKS=OFF
             -DUSE_OPENMP=OFF
             -DUSE_THREAD=OFF
+            -DCMAKE_C_VISIBILITY_PRESET=hidden
         )
 
         # Only pass CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE for single-config generators (it is
